<font color="#FF0000">A DIRTY JOB</font><br>
<tt>Fri Nov 14 21:20:42 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Felt lower than dirt many times.  Last time was in Panama.  Down in the strike zone where the invasion took place.  Looking at all the bombed out buildings that housed the women and children that were shielding the big boys.<br><br>
 Low tide and the mud flats were exposed where the seal team died.  I remember the briefing about the guys stuck up to their waist fighting to the end.  Making the enemy pay until out of ammo and then waiting to die.  Victims of dumb ass planners.  Standing there looking at that sea of mud made me feel dirty.  Still does.<br><br>
So many brave men.  Too little recognition.<br><br>
I choose to remember.
